title: Yevgeny Prigozhin was among passengers on jet that crashed, Russian authorities say
description: Yevgeny Prigozhin, a Russian mercenary chief who led a mutiny against the Kremlin, is listed among the 10 people who were aboard a private jet that crashed outside of Moscow, killing all aboard, Russian aviation authorities reported. NBC News’ Richard Engel reports.

title: U.S. officials draft proposal to ease Venezuela oil sanctions
description: U.S. officials are drafting a proposal that would ease sanctions on Venezuela’s oil sector if the nation moves toward a free and fair presidential election.

title: Putin speaks at WWII memorial amid reports Prigozhin is dead
description: As reports circulated that his former-ally-turned-mutineer Yevgeny Prighozin had been killed in a plane crash, President Vladimir Putin attended an event marking the 80th anniversary of the Battle of Kursk, where he praised Russian forces fighting in Ukraine, saying, “All our soldiers fight bravely and valiantly.”

title: China and Russia challenge U.S. influence at summit of non-Western leaders
description: As China and Russia work to curtail U.S. and Western influence, the BRICS bloc is debating an expansion to increase its power and diminish the dominance of the dollar.

title: Tropical Storm Franklin makes landfall on Haiti and Dominican Republic, triggering fears of deadly landslides
description: Tropical Storm Franklin made landfall Wednesday on the island of Hispaniola shared by the Dominican Republic and Haiti, bringing fears it would trigger deadly landslides and heavy flooding in both countries.

title: U.S.-China tensions may sink key science and technology pact
description: A U.S.-China agreement on cooperation in science and technology is on the verge of lapsing for the first time in decades amid opposition from U.S. lawmakers.

title: Man flees China by riding jet ski hundreds of miles across the sea
description: A man who has been detained since riding a jet ski to South Korea’s Incheon coast is believed to be a Chinese dissident who fled across the Yellow Sea.

title: Russia says latest Ukrainian drone attack on Moscow has been thwarted
description: Russian defenses downed Ukrainian drones in Moscow and the region around the capital early Wednesday, the defense ministry and the mayor said. No casualties were reported.

title: Rappelling commandos and a 900ft drop: How Pakistan's cable car rescue unfolded
description: As he does most days, Umraiz Khan had just walked his son, Irfan, to the cable car he takes to school on the other side of a deep valley in their remote, mountainous region of Pakistan.

title: Video shows jet ski 'Chinese man used to travel to South Korea'
description: South Korea's coast guard said it had detained a Chinese man in his 30s after he had traveled from China on a 1,800 cc jet ski, wearing a life jacket and helmet and carrying a telescope, compass and five containers of fuel.

title: At least 26 killed as railway bridge collapses in India
description: A railway bridge being built in India collapsed on Wednesday killing at least 26 workers and injuring two, police said, as the state-run railway authority opened an investigation.

title: Watch: The moon's surface from India's lunar probe at it flies to landing zone
description: India’s space agency released visuals of the moon taken from its spacecraft ahead of its attempt to land on the lunar surface.

title: Russia says drone attack on Moscow thwarted, 3 killed near Ukrainian border
description: Russia said on Wednesday it had thwarted the latest Ukrainian drone attack on Moscow but three people were killed in a drone strike near the Ukrainian border.

title: 7 students and a teacher rescued from dangling cable car
description: Eight people who were trapped in a disabled cable car dangling high above a valley in Pakistan returned safely to the ground Tuesday after military commandos staged a daring and delicate rescue. NBC News' Claudio Lavanga reports.

title: U.S. commerce secretary set to visit China next week as high-level talks continue
description: U.S. Secretary of Commerce Gina Raimondo is set to visit China from Aug. 27 to 30, both countries announced Tuesday.
